This paper deals with generative models and image generation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks and adversarial training, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which are a type of neural network commonly used in unsupervised learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the preservation of realistic resemblances in the generated images, which suggests that it may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
